# React & TypeScript Conventions

## TypeScript

- Prefer `.ts` and `.tsx` for new files. Do not add new `.js` or `.jsx` files.
- Use proper types; avoid `any` when a concrete type is available.
- Use path aliases: `@/core/*`, `@/modules/*`, `@/components/*`, etc.

## Module Structure (Odoo-like)

All features are self-contained modules under `src/modules/<feature>/`:

```
modules/driver/
├── index.ts           # Module export
├── routes.tsx         # Route definitions
├── menu.ts            # Menu items
├── pages/             # Page components
├── api/               # API calls
└── schemas/           # Zod schemas
```

Each module exports a `FrontModule` that declares routes, menus, and permissions:

```tsx
// modules/driver/index.ts
export const driverModule: FrontModule = {
  name: 'driver',
  routes,
  menu,
  permissions: ['driver.read', 'driver.create', 'driver.update', 'driver.delete']
};
```

## CRUD Pages

Use `CrudPage` from `@/core/crud` for list views (70% less boilerplate):

```tsx
import { CrudPage } from '@/core/crud';

export function DriverListPage() {
  return (
    <CrudPage config={{
      title: 'Drivers',
      queryKey: ['drivers'],
      queryFn: driverApi.list,
      columns: driverColumns,
      permissions: {
        read: 'driver.read',
        create: 'driver.create',
        update: 'driver.update',
        delete: 'driver.delete',
      }
    }} />
  );
}
```

## Page Layout

Use core UI components for consistent layouts:

```tsx
import { Page, PageHeader, PageToolbar, PageContent } from '@/core/ui';

<Page>
  <PageHeader title="My Page" actions={<Button>Action</Button>} />
  <PageToolbar search={search} onSearchChange={setSearch} />
  <PageContent>{/* content */}</PageContent>
</Page>
```

## Permission Guards

Wrap actions and routes with `<Can>` component:

```tsx
import { Can } from '@/core/auth';

<Can permission="driver.create">
  <Button>Add Driver</Button>
</Can>
```

## Folder Structure

- Modules: `src/modules/<feature>/`
- Core systems: `src/core/` (auth, tenant, crud, ui, hooks, api)
- Shared UI: `src/components/` (shadcn/ui)
- Utils: `src/lib/utils.ts` (use `cn()` for class names)
